    "goal": "Make Python 3.8 the declared and continuously verified minimum Better Plan runtime.",
    "description": "Scope: Closure: capability - Python 3.8+ runtime compatibility; own the public runtime declaration, CI version matrix, any required direct source migration, and lower-bound acceptance tests. Context: the repository compiles on Python 3.8 but declares no minimum and CI begins above that floor. Target: one source implementation whose complete behavior passes on CPython 3.8 and current Python, with Linux and Windows lower-bound CI. Design Considerations: use actual interpreter execution as the oracle; replace unsupported APIs directly with Python 3.8 standard-library forms; retain current command and state semantics. Design Value: a tested lower bound is more reliable than annotation inspection or an undocumented compatibility claim. Constraints & Risks: no Python 3.7 support, compatibility dependency, parallel implementation, skipped test, workflow semantic change, private path, raw runtime output, or repeated full regression.",
